Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Knidian pottery transport amphora to sharpish turn. Clay near fine pink-buff; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Name Agestratos Trimmed. The stamp is similar to Grace's KT370, with the same spelling of Agestratos with double gamma, from the fabricant Dionysios.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0353)
